      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add agent-scoped exec environments",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nSpecialized agents currently share the Gateway process environment. Giving one agent a scoped API credential therefore requires process-wide env, wrapper scripts, or a separate deployment, and host exec can inherit unrelated Gateway credentials by default.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\n- Add agent-only `agents.list[].tools.exec.env` values with SecretRef support.\n- Add `inheritHostEnv: false` for a minimal Gateway exec environment and disable shell-startup snapshots in that mode.\n- Keep precedence deterministic: model env < agent env < trusted plugin env < trusted channel context.\n- Bind approval metadata to env keys without serializing Gateway credential values.\n- Reject configured agent env for node-host exec before remote preparation; node credentials must be configured on the node.\n- Redact the wildcard env surface in config snapshots and expose its full SecretInput shape in generated config schema.\n- Preserve POSIX case-sensitive inherited/sandbox env semantics while applying case-folded precedence only when an override targets a key.\n\n## User Impact\n\nOperators can give a specialized agent its own exec-only credentials without adding them to every Gateway child process. Setting `inheritHostEnv: false` further limits ambient credential inheritance. Existing behavior remains the default, and node-host deployments continue to configure credentials on the node itself.\n\nThis scopes subprocess injection; it is not a same-process plugin or same-OS-user security boundary. Any command available to the agent can read the configured values.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Focused agent/config/SecretRef/security suites pass, including agent isolation, approval metadata, schema lookup, redaction, case precedence, stale channel context, node rejection, and inactive node-only SecretRefs.\n- Gateway env-binding approval cases pass.\n- Base config schema, config docs baseline, plugin SDK API baseline, docs MDX, docs links, formatting, lint, and `git diff --check` pass.\n- Independent security/API review is clean after fixes.\n- Repository autoreview rerun after all findings were addressed.\n",
